            <h1>Utilizzare Bootstrap su un’app Express di NodeJS</h1>
            <p><strong>Il link del post:</strong></p>
            <p><a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/30449313/how-do-i-make-a-docker-container-start-automatically-on-system-boot">https://stackoverflow.com/questions/30449313/how-do-i-make-a-docker-container-start-automatically-on-system-boot</a></p>
            <p><strong>Installare</strong> con npm <strong>Bootstrap</strong> e <strong>jQuery</strong> (su cui si basa Bootstrap):</p>
            <p><strong>npm i -D bootstrap jquery</strong></p>
            <p>Ora sarà installato nei node_modules dell’app</p>
            <p>Inserire nell’<strong>index.js</strong> la riga:</p>
            <p><strong>app.use(express.static(__dirname))</strong></p>
            <p>Inserire nel file <strong>.html</strong> o nel mio caso <strong>.ejs</strong>, dove si vuole far applicare lo style, nell’<strong>head</strong>:</p>
            <p><strong>link rel="stylesheet" href="../node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"/</strong></p>
            <br>
            <p>Sempre nello stesso file inserire alla fine del <strong>body</strong>:</p>
            <p><strong>script src="../node_modules/node_modules/jquery/dist/jquery.min.js"</strong></p>
            <p><strong>script src="../node_modules/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.min.js"</strong></p>
